-- Fresnillo Says Profit Falls 25% as Silver Output, Prices Decline
-- B y   T h o m a s   B i e s h e u v e l
-- 2012-07-31T06:12:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-31/fresnillo-says-profit-falls-25-as-silver-output-prices-decline.html
Fresnillo Plc (FRES) , the worldâ€™s biggest
primary silver producer, reported a 25 percent drop in first-
half profit after silver production and prices fell.  Net income slipped to $366.7 million from $488.7 million a
year earlier, Mexico City-based Fresnillo said in a statement
today. Sales dropped 2.7 percent to $1.09 billion.  The company produced 20.1 million ounces of silver in the
first half, 6.5 percent less than a year earlier. The company
said its average selling price dropped 13 percent to $30.97 an
ounce in the period.  The company reiterated its full-year production target of
41 million ounces of silver and 460,000 ounces of gold.  To contact the reporter on this story:
